The lab. exercise for Section A has been given below. You need to complete it in the lab. on Monday, 29.01.2018.

1a. Implement following grammar for variable declaration (e represents null symbol):
vardec->type id opid;
type->char|int|float|double
opid->, id opid|e

Test following declarations:
char id, id;
int id, id, int;
float id

1b. Implement extended grammar of 1a for variable declaration:
vardec->type id opast opid;
type->char|inttype|realtype
inttype->unsigned intver|intver
intver->short int|long int|intf
realtype->float|double|long double
opast->=val|=id opast|e
opid->, id opast opid|e

Test following declarations:
int id=val;
char id,id=id;
unsigned long int id=id=id;
long double;

2a. Write down the algorithm to eliminate left recursion from given grammar.
2b. Write down the algorithm to implement left factoring in given grammar.

3. Implement the algorithm to estimate FIRST() of all the symbols and strings in given grammar.
